What happens on the go with my email?
E-mail is actually called electronic letter.
Was the drafting of the Internet service e-mail similar to the conventional postal service technically the letter secret implemented?
In the conception of the early Internet services, the focus was on making communication possible.
Therefore, the basic technical protocols did not take care to create a stable foundation for a contact-proof exchange of letters.
Therefore, a conventional email is more like an open postcard than a sealed letter.
If user "Anna" sends an email to "Benni", are the computers of the two directly connected?
The email program or the browser of Anna sends the mail to the mail server of your service provider in the first step.
For example, if she has a GMail account, that would be Google.
This mail server sends the content to the provider that Benni uses.
On the route, the mail can run on several other servers on the Internet.
Bennie can then call the content at his provider.
Are traditional emails reading through the net on their way?
Most mails are read several times by software robots on the go.
The provider of the sender usually checks whether the mail carries a malicious program as an attachment.
A virus check is also carried out on the receiver systems.
In addition, the providers check whether it is a troublesome and unwanted spam mail, which is immediately deleted or at least sorted away into a spam folder.
Do the robots have another task?
For systems like GMail, the robot also determines the information that Google needs to place context advertising.
If Anna and Benni communicate via GMail about their upcoming holiday trip, Google can display corresponding links to holiday offers.
Do unknown people also read the emails?
The likelihood of unauthorized persons reading an email is extremely low.
In theory, however, this is possible.
In companies, administrators often have the opportunity to read electronic mail.
Law enforcement and intelligence agencies also have legal options to intercept or take note of email.
In addition, there are possible illegal spying actions.
Is it possible to protect emails against reading?
With encryption according to the OpenPGP standard, an email can be effectively encrypted against reading.
With high technical effort, it is also possible to obscure the metadata of an e-mail communication, so that it is not even possible to readily recognize who has communicated with whom.
How important are Yahoo and Google in the email market in Germany?
Yahoo and Google play only a minor role in the mainly privately used mailboxes, according to an investigation by Convios Consulting from August 2013.
While Yahoo Mail's shares had fallen recently, GMail was able to gain significantly from Google.
